[FILE:430:descriptions/desc.primary]
Brotli is a generic-purpose lossless compression algorithm that compresses
data using a combination of a modern variant of the LZ77 algorithm, Huffman
coding  and 2nd order context modeling, with a compression ratio comparable
to the best  currently available general-purpose compression methods. It is
similar in speed  with deflate but offers more dense compression.

The Brotli Compressed Data Format is specified in RFC 7932.


[FILE:51:descriptions/desc.tools]
This package contains the brotli compression tool.


